commitResults.messageTitle: Modify build.gradle
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, assertions were not enabled and this prevented the use of assertions, therefore critical errors and input requirements could not be swiftly caught.

Now, assertions have been enabled to allow for the use of the assert function, to catch these errors quickly.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add assertions to confirm that inputs for Todo, Deadline or Event tasks are not null
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, if else statements were used to determine whether the input was valid (i.e. not null). This caused more nested code and reduced the code quality, and prevented us from checking for input validity efficiently.

Add assert statements to return an assertion error when the user inputs no arguments for a Todo, Deadline or Event task.

This allows for inputs to be checked in one line, and reduces nested code.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update tests for DeadlineHandler and TodoHandler
commitResults.messageBody: Tests have been updated to match the outputs of the latest update of DeadlineHandler and TodoHandler, and now recgonises the assertion error.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update access modifiers for Task, Deadline, Event
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, there were no access modifiers for some variables in the mentioned classes. This may lead to improper usage of private class variables.

Update the access modifiers for certain variables to be protected or private, as appropriate. Prevents unintentional breaking of the abstraction barrier.

As a step towards prevent unintentional breaking of the abstraction barrier and improper usage of supposedly private variables, let's be more mindful and remember to assign appropriate access variables when creating new variables and methods.
